A circle centered at $O$ has radius 1 and contains the point $A$. Segment $AB$ is tangent to the circle at $A$ and $\angle
AOB=\theta$. If point $C$ lies on $\overline{OA}$ and $\overline{BC}$ bisects $\angle ABO$, then express $OC$ in terms of $s$ and $c,$ where $s = \sin \theta$ and $c = \cos \theta.$

[asy]
pair A,B,C,O;
O=(0,0);
A=(1,0);
C=(0.6,0);
B=(1,2);
label("$\theta$",(0.1,0),NE);
label("$O$",O,S);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$A$",A,E);
label("$B$",B,E);
draw(A--O--B--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(C--B,linewidth(0.7));
draw(Circle(O,1),linewidth(0.7));
[/asy]

inference:
Since $\overline{AB}$ is tangent to the circle at $A,$ $\angle OAB = 90^\circ.$  Since $\overline{BC}$ bisects $\angle ABO,$ $\angle ABC = \angle CBO = \frac{1}{2} \angle ABO = \frac{1}{2} (180^\circ - \theta) = 90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2}.$

[asy]
pair A,B,C,O;
O=(0,0);
A=(1,0);
C=(0.6,0);
B=(1,2);
label("$\theta$",(0.1,0),NE);
label("$O$",O,S);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$A$",A,E);
label("$B$",B,E);
draw(A--O--B--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(C--B,linewidth(0.7));
draw(Circle(O,1),linewidth(0.7));
label("$90^\circ$",A + (0.2,0.1),S);
label("$90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2}$",B + (-0.2,0.3),W);
label("$90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2}$",(B + C)/2,E);
[/asy]

Then $\angle BOC = 180^\circ - \angle ABC - \angle CBO = 180^\circ - \left( 90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2} \right) - \left( 90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2} \right) = \theta.$  Also, $OA = 1,$ so by the Law of Sines on triangle $BOC,$
\[\frac{OC}{\sin \angle OBC} = \frac{OB}{\sin \angle BOC}.\]Then
\[OC = \frac{OB \sin \angle OBC}{\sin \angle BOC} = \frac{OB \sin \left( 90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2} \right)}{\sin \theta} = \frac{OB \cos \frac{\theta}{2}}{\sin \theta}.\]By the Law of Cosines on triangle $ABO,$
\[OB^2 = OA^2 + AB^2 - 2 \cdot OA \cdot AB \cdot \cos \angle OAB = 1 + AB^2,\]so $OB = \sqrt{1 + AB^2}.$

[asy]
pair A,B,C,O;
O=(0,0);
A=(1,0);
C=(0.6,0);
B=(1,2);
label("$\theta$",(0.1,0),NE);
label("$O$",O,S);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$A$",A,E);
label("$B$",B,E);
draw(A--O--B--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(C--B,linewidth(0.7));
draw(Circle(O,1),linewidth(0.7));
label("$90^\circ$",A + (0.2,0.1),S);
label("$90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2}$",B + (-0.2,0.3),W);
label("$90^\circ - \frac{\theta}{2}$",(B + C)/2,E);
label("$1$",(A + O)/2,S);
label("$AB$",A + (B + A)/2,NE);
label("$OB$",(O + B)/2,NW);
[/asy]

Since $\angle OAB = 90^\circ,$
\[\sin \angle OAB = \sin 90^\circ = 1 = \frac{AB}{OB},\]so $AB = OB.$  Hence, $OB = \sqrt{1 + OB^2},$ so $OB^2 = 1 + OB^2.$  This means $OB^2 = -1,$ which is impossible, so $OB$ must be undefined.  Therefore, $OC$ is also undefined.

